President Trump visited the Shell Pennsylvania Petrochemicals Complex in Monaca, Pennsylvania. He praised the plant and its workers, mentioning the employment opportunities it provides. The president also highlighted the large cranes at the facility, calling them among the largest in the world. Shell representatives explained the process of turning ethane into ethylene and then producing polyethylene. The president commended Shell for buying equipment from American manufacturers, particularly mentioning Maine. He also noted that the plant receives supplies via the Ohio River and ships products by rail and truck. President Trump emphasized the quality and importance of the facility and expressed hope for future projects. The visit concluded with the president thanking everyone and Secretary Perry mentioning a big project announcement for the following week.